citation.case_name: IL FY Co. v. Temporary State Housing Rent Comm'n

html:
369 U.S. 795

82 S.Ct. 1155

8 L.Ed.2d 285

I. L. F. Y. CO.
v.
TEMPORARY STATE HOUSING RENT COMMISSION et al.

No. 569.

Supreme Court of the United States

May 21, 1962

Robert S. Fougner, for appellant.

Harold Zucker, Robert E. Herman and Edward V. Alfieri, for appellee State Rent Commission.

PER CURIAM.

1

The motion to dismiss is granted and the appeal is dismissed for want of a substantial federal question.

2

Mr. Justice FRANKFURTER took no part in the consideration or decision of this case.
